body:
Actually, Artemis executes stopAll tasks. At the very least, I have confirmed that the run function in the shutdown hook gets called. 

To test that the shutdown hook and the run function gets called, I added a write to file call to the run function in Artemis.java, as shown below, and a similar write to file call to the stopAll function in ServiceController.java :
```
// Detect SIGTERM
Runtime.getRuntime().addShutdownHook(new Thread(){
  @Override
  public void run(){
    List<String> lines = Arrays.asList("The first line", "The second line");
    Path file = Paths.get("FIRST_FILE.txt");
    try{
      Files.write(file, lines, Charset.forName("UTF-8"));
    } 
    catch (IOException e){
      System.out.println("IO Error");
    }
    System.out.println("Artemis is shutting down");
    ServiceController.stopAll(cliArgs);
  }
});
````
Now when I ran and hit ctrl-c, I saw both of these test files being written. So I know that the shutdown hook and functions passed to it gets called. However, I don't know why print statements don't show up. 

